<p>I’m an Associate Professor at the <a href="http://literatura.uniandes.edu.co/">Department of Literature</a>, <a href="https://uniandes.edu.co/">Universidad de los Andes</a>, Bogotá, Colombia. My teaching and research interests concern classic and medieval works and authors from the Western (Latin) tradition. I’m an advocate of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_humanities">digital humanities</a> as well.</p>

<p>I’m also adjunct editor of the <a href="https://scta.lombardpress.org/#/text?resourceid=http://scta.info/resource/b1-d3-qun">Online Digital Edition of Wodeham’s <em>Ordinatio</em></a>, under the direction of Prof <a href="http://jeffreycwitt.com/">Jeffrey C. Witt</a>.</p>

<p>You can check out my Academia page <a href="https://uniandes.academia.edu/NicolasVaughan">here</a>.</p>

<p>I’m an enthusiast of the <a href="https://www.python.org/">Python programming language</a>, as well as of the document preparation system and markup language <a href="https://www.latex-project.org//">LaTeX</a>. You may find some programmes and packages I have written in and for Python and LaTeX at my <a href="https://gitlab.com/nivaca">gitlab page</a>. I created this site with the static blogging platform <a href="http://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a>, using a nice theme by <a href="https://github.com/svmiller">Steve V. Miller</a>, and it is hosted as a <a href="https://gitlab.com/help/user/project/pages/index.md">gitlab page</a>.</p>

<p>I only use <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU/Linux_naming_controversy">GNU/Linux</a> OS on my machines. Both at home and at the office I use <a href="https://manjaro.org">Manjaro Linux</a> with the powerful <a href="https://www.kde.org/plasma-desktop">KDE Plasma</a> desktop.</p>
